ra Durga Ashtami, devotees wake up early in the morning and take a ritualistic bath. They then offer prayers to the Goddess, usually in the form of a small idol or image. Special bhajans and hymns are sung in praise of Goddess Durga, and devotees observe a fast throughout the day. In the evening, aarti is performed, and prasad is distributed among family members and devotees. The rituals and celebrations associated with Chaitra Durga Ashtami are a way for devotees to express their devotion and seek the blessings of the Goddess. By observing the rituals and traditions, devotees can strengthen their faith and spiritual connection with the divine. <\/p><p><strong>Symbolism of Mahagauri <\/strong><\/p><p>Mahagauri, the eighth form of Goddess Durga, is depicted as having a fair complexion and wearing white clothes. She is often depicted riding a bull and holding a trishul (trident) and a damaru (drum) in her hands. Mahagauri is believed to bestow peace, prosperity, and happiness upon her devotees and remove all obstacles from their lives. The symbolism of Mahagauri is deeply rooted in Hindu mythology. Her fair complexion and white clothes represent purity and spirituality, while her trishul and damaru represent her power and authority. The bull she rides symbolizes strength and determination, while the trident and drum represent her ability to destroy evil and create harmony. <\/p><p><strong>Importance of Fasting <\/strong><\/p><p>Fasting on Chaitra Durga Ashtami is considered auspicious and is believed to cleanse the body and mind. Devotees abstain from consuming food and water throughout the day and break their fast only after performing the evening aarti. Fasting is believed to invoke the blessings of the Goddess and bring health and prosperity to the devotees. Fasting is a way for devotees to express their devotion and seek the blessings of the Goddess. By abstaining from food and water, devotees can purify their bodies and minds and strengthen their spiritual connection with the divine. Chaitra Durga Ashtami is a festival that celebrates the power and grace of Goddess Durga. By observing the rituals and traditions associated with the festival, devotees can strengthen their faith and spiritual connection with the divine. The festival is a time for devotees to come together, pray, and seek the blessings of the Goddess for a prosperous and fulfilling life.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Ashtami Tithi begins at 12:11 on April 15, 2024, and ends at 13:23 on April 16, 2024. The best time for pooja on Ashtami tomorrow is between 9:00 AM and 12:00 PM, which falls&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":575,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[29],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-746","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-gurus-saadhus-kathas-mythology-en"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/746"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=746"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/746\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/575"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=746"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=746"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dhaarmi.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=746"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":tru